file=Product/ux/operational/tool/ux-tool-requirements.md · u—t:ux — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; it does not grant them.** Access is configured at deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply — registered tools only, least privilege, PII minimized).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| research-repository \| file read/write (own repo); read (PRD/experiment IDs for linking) \| the reuse-first memory \| · tb=\| study-design \| file write (study plans); recruit/scheduling channel (if configured) \| protocol + sample \| · tb=\| synthesis-discipline \| file read (raw study data); file write (confidence-flagged claims → repo) \| data → claims \| · tb=\| voice-of-customer-intake \| READ-ONLY on configured VoC feeds (support/reviews/NPS); file write (tagged verbatims → repo) \| standing listening pipeline \| · u—t:ux — Tool Requirements=ux reads evidence sources and writes only its own repository/plans; VoC feeds are read-only (Client Success owns tickets); PII is minimized at ingest (Rail 2). Behavioral Science theory is a flagged dependency, never inlined.\n